args:
When Grace is caught in a trap after attempting
to infiltrate the Syndicate base, Farren rushes
onto the scene and announces that he still
wants to help people despite not knowing his
reason for fighting. Afterward, he challenges
his former friend Jake to a showdown.
(There are few soldiers about the base...\nIt seems the fuss in the village has made\nfor a fine distraction.)
(Time to gather what intelligence I can\nwhile the moment is ripe.)
(...All right. I think I have a general sense\nof the Wyrmbound Soldier Project now.)
(But as always, no more than scraps and\nfragments regarding the leadership.)
(Still, I've overstayed my welcome.\nTime to secure an escape roâ€”)
He's protected by a magical barrier.\nThis will take some time to dispel,\nbut regardless, I have to try.
Oh, I don't think that will be necessary.
I'm in your debt for what went down in the\nvillage, traitor. It really helped to have you\ntake the bait as aggressively as you did.
Didn't bring the little duck with you, eh?\nWell, can't say as I blame youâ€”that one\nwas nothing but trouble from the start.
Still, waltzing in here all alone displays\na surprising level of optimism.
Oh, I wouldn't be so sure about that.\nYou really should consider the possibility\nthat he and I are operating separately.
Even if he IS in this base somewhere,\nhe's nothing but a helpless kid without\nhis B-Unit.
Sadly, you've learned far too much about\nwyrmbinding for me to let you leave this\nplace alive.
If you so much as lift a finger against me,\nI'll make you and your friends go berserk\nand attack each other again.
Hold positions! If she could've done that,\nshe would've done so already.
(...Urgh. He saw through my bluff. I hate to\nadmit it, but I'm in real trouble here...)
Attack, wyrmbound! This time, we prove\nour power to the Syndicate for true!
(I am sorry, my beloved, but I can't come\nto you just yet. Protect me!)
What are you doing here, Farren?!\nI told you to return to the Halidom!
I thought about what you saidâ€”about my\nreasons for fighting and living?
But what's wrong with fighting for no\nreason other than helping others?!
I may not have some special purpose or\nultimate goal I'm pursuing, but that doesn't\nmean I can ignore my desire to help.
You're right: I feel guilty that I lived while\nother people didn't.

I woke up every day in that Syndicate
prison convinced it would be my last.
And while I wasn't looking to die, I guess
I just sort of...got used to the idea.
But I realized something: All the people\nwho helped me didn't sacrifice themselves\nfor my sake.
They put their lives on the line for their\nown sakes, which is why I'm going to do\nthe same thing!
I'm going to fight for my own personal\ndesire to help!
It seems that you are both stronger and\nmore thick-skulled that I ever imagined.

Still, I suppose there's nothing for it at
this very moment, so I'll save both my
scolding and my thanks until we are all
safely ensconced back at the Halidom.
Now that sounds like a plan!

Well, this has all been very tear-jerking
and emotional, but you left out the part
where you have to actually...you know.
Deal with us?
The traitor's trick won't work this time,\nand the little duck is nothing but a dead\nduck without his B-Unit!
Your future is death, and nothing will ever\nchange that!
I wouldn't be so sure about that.
Lil' Barb! Oh, it's so good to see you!\nDid you escape?
I mean, not really? Nothing I did, at any\nrate. Somebody just sorta let me out.
Then we have an ally who is also\ninfiltrating this base? Who?!
No idea, lady. I didn't recognize 'em,\nand they didn't bother with a name.
Whatever happened, it's great to have\nyou back! You ready to fight?
You bet! Step up, punks, 'cause I'm gonna\nmake you regret the day you were born!
We'll crush every last one'a ya!

Well, this is just sad. What makes you
think you can defeat me when I squashed
you like a couple of bugs the last time
we danced?
'Cause we ain't losing this time, bucko.\nNow get your mean face on, Farren!
I won't hold back this time, Jake!
Implying that you were before? Ha!\nLet's see how big you talk after I wipe\nthe floor with your face!
